{
  "description": "A close-up shot focuses on the underside of a vibrant red tulip blossom. The perspective is from below, looking up into the flower's interior. The petals are a rich, saturated red, transitioning to a warm yellow-orange towards the center where the stamen and pistil would be. The stem is a muted green and visible at the bottom of the frame. The lighting is soft and diffused, creating highlights and shadows that emphasize the flower's texture and form. A blurred red tulip is visible in the left corner, hinting at a bouquet or grouping. The background is out of focus, providing a gentle contrast and drawing attention to the primary blossom.",
